The paper proposes data structures for solving the shortest unique substring (SUS) problem, which is a problem in string algorithms and data structures. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves some combinatorial and information-theoretic analysis, which suggests categories such as cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also discusses the space complexity of the proposed data structures, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper proposes output-sensitive algorithms, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
